div.p: F74/12031, unit 258, VPRS 3992/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.

To proof.
Location can't be right. See also M to R. Ramsay, 31 May 1875. This letter was registered in the Education Department as H5970.
Melbourne, 22/9/74.

In reply to your letter N. 5871
T. Ware to M, 21 September 1874. I have the honor to inform you for information of the hon. Rob Ramsay, that I can manage to provide a set of the educational collections for the contributors towards this issue from spare specimens still available here, so that the copies still available at your Office may not be reduced, as likely many further calls will be made for supply.
Thanking Mr Ramsay and yourself for the exertions of bringing these plants at such very appropriate places under permanent notice,

Ferd. von Mueller.
On 6 September 1876, […] noted: 'Part III now ready. Will it be necessary to forwd by Circular? As to mode of transmission see minute by Mr Francis of 26-6-74. (50 Institutes will probably ask to be supplied.)' see if a p/c of this is in the files.
